{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0021-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Tags & Classification",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738454400000,
  "modified": 1773243817475,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Tags in Hobson are a universal classification system. Any item can be tagged. Tags themselves are items, enabling metadata, hierarchy, and rich queries."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Core Concept: Any Item as Tag"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "There is no dedicated \"tag type.\" Any item can serve as a tag — a note, a project, a concept. An item is \"tagged with\" another item by including its ID in "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.tags"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ":"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "{\n  id: \"my-note-uuid\",\n  type: \"note-type-uuid\",\n  content: {\n    description: \"Some note content\",\n    tags: [\"project-uuid\", \"urgent-tag-uuid\", \"concept-uuid\"]\n  }\n}"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "This means tags are just items you reference. No special infrastructure needed."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Tag Discovery Algorithm"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "To find items tagged with a given tag, query all items whose "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.tags"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " array includes the tag's ID:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "const tagged = await api.query(item =>\n  item.content?.tags?.includes(tagId)\n);"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Hierarchical Tags via "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.parent"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Tags can form hierarchies through the "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.parent"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " property:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "Hobson (parent: null)\n├── Hobson/kernel (parent: hobson-tag-id)\n├── Hobson/views (parent: hobson-tag-id)\n└── Hobson/idea (parent: hobson-tag-id)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Tag queries can walk parent chains to find all items under a category:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "async function isDescendantOf(tagId, ancestorId) {\n  let current = tagId;\n  const visited = new Set();\n  while (current && !visited.has(current)) {\n    if (current === ancestorId) return true;\n    visited.add(current);\n    const tag = await api.get(current);\n    current = tag?.content?.parent;\n  }\n  return false;\n}"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Tag Browser"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Views can display items organized by their tags. The spatial canvas view supports a tag sidebar that shows hierarchical tags and filters the displayed items."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Tag Editing UI"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "field-view-tags"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " field view provides tag editing: search existing tags, create new ones, remove tags. It's used by "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "generic-view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " when rendering the "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "tags"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " field."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Design Rationale"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Not a Dedicated Tag Type?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A dedicated tag type would be simpler but limiting:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Any item can already serve as a classification marker"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Projects, people, concepts — all natural tags without a special type"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Tag metadata (color, description) is just item content"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Tag hierarchy is just "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "content.parent"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — works on any item"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Not Relationship Items?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "\"Note A is tagged with Work\" — the \"is tagged with\" doesn't add semantic meaning. It's classification, not a relationship. Compare with \"Note A follows on from Note B\" where the relationship type carries important information."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Therefore: tags as references in an array, relationships as first-class items."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Universal (Not Note-Specific)?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Consistent with \"everything is an item\" philosophy"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Cross-cutting queries (\"show me all urgent items\") work across types"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Different users tag different things — the system shouldn't restrict this"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
